{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":959,"text":"The job of uncovering the global food waste scandal"},{"time":3717,"text":"started for me when I was 15 years old."},{"time":6735,"text":"I bought some pigs. I was living in Sussex."},{"time":9256,"text":"And I started to feed them in the most traditional"},{"time":11639,"text":"and environmentally friendly way."},{"time":13610,"text":"I went to my school kitchen, and I said,"},{"time":15935,"text":"\"Give me the scraps that my school friends have turned"},{"time":17481,"text":"their noses up at.\""},{"time":18347,"text":"I went to the local baker and took their stale bread."},{"time":21011,"text":"I went to the local greengrocer, and I went to a farmer"},{"time":23743,"text":"who was throwing away potatoes because they were"},{"time":25581,"text":"the wrong shape or size for supermarkets."},{"time":28767,"text":"This was great. My pigs turned that food waste"},{"time":31856,"text":"into delicious pork. I sold that pork"},{"time":34513,"text":"to my school friends' parents, and I made"},{"time":36500,"text":"a good pocket money addition to my teenage allowance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41137,"text":"But I noticed that most of the food that I was giving my pigs"},{"time":44019,"text":"was in fact fit for human consumption,"},{"time":46402,"text":"and that I was only scratching the surface,"},{"time":48671,"text":"and that right the way up the food supply chain,"},{"time":51533,"text":"in supermarkets, greengrocers, bakers, in our homes,"},{"time":54751,"text":"in factories and farms, we were hemorrhaging out food."},{"time":58011,"text":"Supermarkets didn't even want to talk to me"},{"time":60608,"text":"about how much food they were wasting."},{"time":61982,"text":"I'd been round the back. I'd seen bins full of food"},{"time":64466,"text":"being locked and then trucked off to landfill sites,"},{"time":67217,"text":"and I thought, surely there is something more sensible"},{"time":70238,"text":"to do with food than waste it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73405,"text":"One morning, when I was feeding my pigs,"},{"time":75710,"text":"I noticed a particularly tasty-looking sun-dried tomato loaf"},{"time":79397,"text":"that used to crop up from time to time."},{"time":81472,"text":"I grabbed hold of it,"},{"time":82874,"text":"sat down, and ate my breakfast with my pigs. (Laughter)"},{"time":86420,"text":"That was the first act of what I later learned to call freeganism,"},{"time":89540,"text":"really an exhibition of the injustice of food waste,"},{"time":93795,"text":"and the provision of the solution to food waste,"},{"time":96145,"text":"which is simply to sit down and eat food,"},{"time":98799,"text":"rather than throwing it away."},{"time":100287,"text":"That became, as it were, a way of confronting"},{"time":103566,"text":"large businesses in the business of wasting food,"},{"time":106553,"text":"and exposing, most importantly, to the public,"},{"time":109074,"text":"that when we're talking about food being thrown away,"},{"time":111244,"text":"we're not talking about rotten stuff, we're not talking about"},{"time":113383,"text":"stuff that's beyond the pale."},{"time":116095,"text":"We're talking about good, fresh food that is being wasted"},{"time":118211,"text":"on a colossal scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120749,"text":"Eventually, I set about writing my book,"},{"time":122606,"text":"really to demonstrate the extent of this problem"},{"time":124660,"text":"on a global scale. What this shows is"},{"time":128056,"text":"a nation-by-nation breakdown of the likely level"},{"time":131535,"text":"of food waste in each country in the world."},{"time":134637,"text":"Unfortunately, empirical data, good, hard stats, don't exist,"},{"time":138525,"text":"and therefore to prove my point, I first of all had to find"},{"time":141007,"text":"some proxy way of uncovering"},{"time":143160,"text":"how much food was being wasted."},{"time":145405,"text":"So I took the food supply of every single country"},{"time":147961,"text":"and I compared it to what was actually likely"},{"time":151003,"text":"to be being consumed in each country."},{"time":153035,"text":"That's based on diet intake surveys, it's based on"},{"time":156922,"text":"levels of obesity, it's based on a range of factors"},{"time":159588,"text":"that gives you an approximate guess"},{"time":160930,"text":"as to how much food is actually going into people's mouths."},{"time":164157,"text":"That black line in the middle of that table"},{"time":166886,"text":"is the likely level of consumption"},{"time":169882,"text":"with an allowance for certain levels of inevitable waste."},{"time":174244,"text":"There will always be waste. I'm not that unrealistic"},{"time":176163,"text":"that I think we can live in a waste-free world."},{"time":178143,"text":"But that black line shows what a food supply should be"},{"time":182016,"text":"in a country if they allow for a good, stable, secure,"},{"time":186470,"text":"nutritional diet for every person in that country."},{"time":190219,"text":"Any dot above that line, and you'll quickly notice that"},{"time":192626,"text":"that includes most countries in the world,"},{"time":195327,"text":"represents unnecessary surplus, and is likely to reflect"},{"time":199616,"text":"levels of waste in each country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202238,"text":"As a country gets richer, it invests more and more"},{"time":205507,"text":"in getting more and more surplus"},{"time":206798,"text":"into its shops and restaurants,"},{"time":209608,"text":"and as you can see, most European"},{"time":211664,"text":"and North American countries"},{"time":213076,"text":"fall between 150 and 200 percent"},{"time":216216,"text":"of the nutritional requirements of their populations."},{"time":219596,"text":"So a country like America has twice as much food"},{"time":222004,"text":"on its shop shelves and in its restaurants"},{"time":224608,"text":"than is actually required to feed the American people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228176,"text":"But the thing that really struck me,"},{"time":229736,"text":"when I plotted all this data, and it was a lot of numbers,"},{"time":233951,"text":"was that you can see how it levels off."},{"time":237617,"text":"Countries rapidly shoot towards that 150 mark,"},{"time":240685,"text":"and then they level off, and they don't really go on rising"},{"time":243973,"text":"as you might expect."},{"time":245519,"text":"So I decided to unpack that data a little bit further"},{"time":248064,"text":"to see if that was true or false."},{"time":250349,"text":"And that's what I came up with."},{"time":251843,"text":"If you include not just the food that ends up"},{"time":253770,"text":"in shops and restaurants, but also the food"},{"time":255894,"text":"that people feed to livestock,"},{"time":258050,"text":"the maize, the soy, the wheat, that humans could eat"},{"time":261553,"text":"but choose to fatten livestock instead to produce"},{"time":264034,"text":"increasing amounts of meat and dairy products,"},{"time":265965,"text":"what you find is that most rich countries"},{"time":267632,"text":"have between three and four times the amount of food"},{"time":271955,"text":"that their population needs to feed itself."},{"time":275039,"text":"A country like America has four times the amount of food"},{"time":278322,"text":"that it needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281284,"text":"When people talk about the need to increase global"},{"time":284246,"text":"food production to feed those nine billion people"},{"time":286906,"text":"that are expected on the planet by 2050,"},{"time":289418,"text":"I always think of these graphs."},{"time":291139,"text":"The fact is, we have an enormous buffer"},{"time":294090,"text":"in rich countries between ourselves and hunger."},{"time":297971,"text":"We've never had such gargantuan surpluses before."},{"time":302647,"text":"In many ways, this is a great success story"},{"time":305313,"text":"of human civilization, of the agricultural surpluses"},{"time":309452,"text":"that we set out to achieve 12,000 years ago."},{"time":312805,"text":"It is a success story. It has been a success story."},{"time":316362,"text":"But what we have to recognize now is that we are"},{"time":318899,"text":"reaching the ecological limits that our planet can bear,"},{"time":322531,"text":"and when we chop down forests, as we are every day,"},{"time":325168,"text":"to grow more and more food,"},{"time":326516,"text":"when we extract water from depleting water reserves,"},{"time":330264,"text":"when we emit fossil fuel emissions in the quest"},{"time":333652,"text":"to grow more and more food,"},{"time":334944,"text":"and then we throw away so much of it,"},{"time":337795,"text":"we have to think about what we can start saving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340731,"text":"And yesterday, I went to one of the local supermarkets"},{"time":344456,"text":"that I often visit to"},{"time":346672,"text":"inspect, if you like, what they're throwing away."},{"time":350853,"text":"I found quite a few packets of biscuits amongst"},{"time":353256,"text":"all the fruit and vegetables and everything else"},{"time":354883,"text":"that was in there."},{"time":355830,"text":"And I thought, well this could serve as a symbol for today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358270,"text":"So I want you to imagine that these nine biscuits"},{"time":360705,"text":"that I found in the bin represent the global food supply,"},{"time":364233,"text":"okay? We start out with nine."},{"time":365834,"text":"That's what's in fields around the world every single year."},{"time":369317,"text":"The first biscuit we're going to lose"},{"time":371078,"text":"before we even leave the farm."},{"time":372837,"text":"That's a problem primarily associated with"},{"time":376102,"text":"developing work agriculture, whether it's"},{"time":377766,"text":"a lack of infrastructure, refrigeration, pasteurization,"},{"time":380271,"text":"grain stores, even basic fruit crates, which means"},{"time":383184,"text":"that food goes to waste before it even leaves the fields."},{"time":386933,"text":"The next three biscuits are the foods that we decide"},{"time":390429,"text":"to feed to livestock, the maize, the wheat and the soya."},{"time":394169,"text":"Unfortunately, our beasts are inefficient animals,"},{"time":399013,"text":"and they turn two-thirds of that into feces and heat,"},{"time":403188,"text":"so we've lost those two, and we've only kept this one"},{"time":405806,"text":"in meat and dairy products."},{"time":408040,"text":"Two more we're going to throw away directly into bins."},{"time":411624,"text":"This is what most of us think of when we think"},{"time":413177,"text":"of food waste, what ends up in the garbage,"},{"time":415688,"text":"what ends up in supermarket bins,"},{"time":417536,"text":"what ends up in restaurant bins. We've lost another two,"},{"time":420266,"text":"and we've left ourselves with just four biscuits to feed on."},{"time":424024,"text":"That is not a superlatively efficient use of global resources,"},{"time":427823,"text":"especially when you think of the billion hungry people"},{"time":430283,"text":"that exist already in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432423,"text":"Having gone through the data, I then needed"},{"time":434406,"text":"to demonstrate where that food ends up."},{"time":438084,"text":"Where does it end up? We're used to seeing the stuff"},{"time":439703,"text":"on our plates, but what about all the stuff"},{"time":441606,"text":"that goes missing in between?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443546,"text":"Supermarkets are an easy place to start."},{"time":445958,"text":"This is the result of my hobby,"},{"time":448549,"text":"which is unofficial bin inspections. (Laughter)"},{"time":453025,"text":"Strange you might think, but if we could rely on corporations"},{"time":455622,"text":"to tell us what they were doing in the back of their stores,"},{"time":458730,"text":"we wouldn't need to go sneaking around the back,"},{"time":461214,"text":"opening up bins and having a look at what's inside."},{"time":463770,"text":"But this is what you can see more or less on"},{"time":465730,"text":"every street corner in Britain, in Europe, in North America."},{"time":469242,"text":"It represents a colossal waste of food,"},{"time":472308,"text":"but what I discovered whilst I was writing my book"},{"time":474810,"text":"was that this very evident abundance of waste"},{"time":478154,"text":"was actually the tip of the iceberg."},{"time":481098,"text":"When you start going up the supply chain,"},{"time":483154,"text":"you find where the real food waste is happening"},{"time":486140,"text":"on a gargantuan scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488127,"text":"Can I have a show of hands"},{"time":489600,"text":"if you have a loaf of sliced bread in your house?"},{"time":494058,"text":"Who lives in a household where that crust --"},{"time":495977,"text":"that slice at the first and last end of each loaf --"},{"time":499170,"text":"who lives in a household where it does get eaten?"},{"time":501614,"text":"Okay, most people, not everyone, but most people,"},{"time":503981,"text":"and this is, I'm glad to say, what I see across the world,"},{"time":506437,"text":"and yet has anyone seen a supermarket or sandwich shop"},{"time":509226,"text":"anywhere in the world that serves sandwiches"},{"time":511462,"text":"with crusts on it? (Laughter)"},{"time":513236,"text":"I certainly haven't."},{"time":514819,"text":"So I kept on thinking, where do those crusts go? (Laughter)"},{"time":519987,"text":"This is the answer, unfortunately:"},{"time":522202,"text":"13,000 slices of fresh bread coming out of"},{"time":524114,"text":"this one single factory every single day, day-fresh bread."},{"time":529715,"text":"In the same year that I visited this factory,"},{"time":531224,"text":"I went to Pakistan, where people in 2008 were going hungry"},{"time":535674,"text":"as a result of a squeeze on global food supplies."},{"time":539451,"text":"We contribute to that squeeze"},{"time":541635,"text":"by depositing food in bins here in Britain"},{"time":544627,"text":"and elsewhere in the world. We take food"},{"time":546834,"text":"off the market shelves that hungry people depend on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549940,"text":"Go one step up, and you get to farmers,"},{"time":552490,"text":"who throw away sometimes a third or even more"},{"time":554650,"text":"of their harvest because of cosmetic standards."},{"time":556695,"text":"This farmer, for example, has invested 16,000 pounds"},{"time":559618,"text":"in growing spinach, not one leaf of which he harvested,"},{"time":563042,"text":"because there was a little bit of grass growing in amongst it."},{"time":565496,"text":"Potatoes that are cosmetically imperfect,"},{"time":567976,"text":"all going for pigs."},{"time":569509,"text":"Parsnips that are too small for supermarket specifications,"},{"time":573547,"text":"tomatoes in Tenerife,"},{"time":575563,"text":"oranges in Florida,"},{"time":577368,"text":"bananas in Ecuador, where I visited last year,"},{"time":580372,"text":"all being discarded. This is one day's waste"},{"time":582787,"text":"from one banana plantation in Ecuador."},{"time":585324,"text":"All being discarded, perfectly edible,"},{"time":587532,"text":"because they're the wrong shape or size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590020,"text":"If we do that to fruit and vegetables,"},{"time":591600,"text":"you bet we can do it to animals too."},{"time":594415,"text":"Liver, lungs, heads, tails,"},{"time":597154,"text":"kidneys, testicles,"},{"time":599132,"text":"all of these things which are traditional,"},{"time":600845,"text":"delicious and nutritious parts of our gastronomy"},{"time":603660,"text":"go to waste. Offal consumption has halved"},{"time":607156,"text":"in Britain and America in the last 30 years."},{"time":609691,"text":"As a result, this stuff gets fed to dogs at best,"},{"time":612331,"text":"or is incinerated."},{"time":614100,"text":"This man, in Kashgar, Xinjiang province, in Western China,"},{"time":617947,"text":"is serving up his national dish."},{"time":619862,"text":"It's called sheep's organs."},{"time":621577,"text":"It's delicious, it's nutritious,"},{"time":623244,"text":"and as I learned when I went to Kashgar,"},{"time":625652,"text":"it symbolizes their taboo against food waste."},{"time":628721,"text":"I was sitting in a roadside cafe."},{"time":630917,"text":"A chef came to talk to me, I finished my bowl,"},{"time":633521,"text":"and halfway through the conversation, he stopped talking"},{"time":635286,"text":"and he started frowning into my bowl."},{"time":637852,"text":"I thought, \"My goodness, what taboo have I broken?"},{"time":639731,"text":"How have I insulted my host?\""},{"time":641325,"text":"He pointed at three grains of rice"},{"time":643063,"text":"at the bottom of my bowl, and he said, \"Clean.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":647347,"text":"I thought, \"My God, you know, I go around the world"},{"time":649259,"text":"telling people to stop wasting food."},{"time":650675,"text":"This guy has thrashed me at my own game.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655724,"text":"But it gave me faith. It gave me faith that we, the people,"},{"time":658947,"text":"do have the power to stop this tragic waste of resources"},{"time":663983,"text":"if we regard it as socially unacceptable"},{"time":666183,"text":"to waste food on a colossal scale,"},{"time":667687,"text":"if we make noise about it, tell corporations about it,"},{"time":670255,"text":"tell governments we want to see an end to food waste,"},{"time":672875,"text":"we do have the power to bring about that change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675371,"text":"Fish, 40 to 60 percent of European fish"},{"time":678083,"text":"are discarded at sea, they don't even get landed."},{"time":681164,"text":"In our homes, we've lost touch with food."},{"time":683856,"text":"This is an experiment I did on three lettuces."},{"time":686773,"text":"Who keeps lettuces in their fridge?"},{"time":689411,"text":"Most people. The one on the left"},{"time":692987,"text":"was kept in a fridge for 10 days."},{"time":694440,"text":"The one in the middle, on my kitchen table. Not much difference."},{"time":696659,"text":"The one on the right I treated like cut flowers."},{"time":699234,"text":"It's a living organism, cut the slice off,"},{"time":701416,"text":"stuck it in a vase of water,"},{"time":702859,"text":"it was all right for another two weeks after this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706407,"text":"Some food waste, as I said at the beginning,"},{"time":708366,"text":"will inevitably arise, so the question is,"},{"time":710198,"text":"what is the best thing to do with it?"},{"time":712396,"text":"I answered that question when I was 15."},{"time":713902,"text":"In fact, humans answered that question 6,000 years ago:"},{"time":719312,"text":"We domesticated pigs"},{"time":721524,"text":"to turn food waste back into food."},{"time":724296,"text":"And yet, in Europe, that practice has become illegal"},{"time":728027,"text":"since 2001 as a result of the foot-and-mouth outbreak."},{"time":731314,"text":"It's unscientific. It's unnecessary."},{"time":733215,"text":"If you cook food for pigs, just as if"},{"time":735898,"text":"you cook food for humans, it is rendered safe."},{"time":738867,"text":"It's also a massive saving of resources."},{"time":741427,"text":"At the moment, Europe depends on importing"},{"time":744322,"text":"millions of tons of soy from South America,"},{"time":745988,"text":"where its production contributes to global warming,"},{"time":748874,"text":"to deforestation, to biodiversity loss,"},{"time":751474,"text":"to feed livestock here in Europe."},{"time":753921,"text":"At the same time we throw away millions of tons"},{"time":756223,"text":"of food waste which we could and should be feeding them."},{"time":759442,"text":"If we did that, and fed it to pigs, we would save"},{"time":762304,"text":"that amount of carbon."},{"time":764655,"text":"If we feed our food waste which is the current"},{"time":767747,"text":"government favorite way of getting rid of food waste,"},{"time":770042,"text":"to anaerobic digestion, which turns food waste"},{"time":772843,"text":"into gas to produce electricity,"},{"time":775147,"text":"you save a paltry 448 kilograms of carbon dioxide"},{"time":778880,"text":"per ton of food waste. It's much better to feed it to pigs."},{"time":781362,"text":"We knew that during the war. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784622,"text":"A silver lining: It has kicked off globally,"},{"time":788896,"text":"the quest to tackle food waste."},{"time":790666,"text":"Feeding the 5,000 is an event I first organized in 2009."},{"time":794520,"text":"We fed 5,000 people all on food that otherwise"},{"time":796776,"text":"would have been wasted."},{"time":798174,"text":"Since then, it's happened again in London,"},{"time":800474,"text":"it's happening internationally, and across the country."},{"time":802607,"text":"It's a way of organizations coming together"},{"time":804950,"text":"to celebrate food, to say the best thing to do with food"},{"time":808692,"text":"is to eat and enjoy it, and to stop wasting it."},{"time":811499,"text":"For the sake of the planet we live on,"},{"time":814092,"text":"for the sake of our children,"},{"time":817372,"text":"for the sake of all the other"},{"time":818942,"text":"organisms that share our planet with us,"},{"time":821390,"text":"we are a terrestrial animal, and we depend on our land"},{"time":824431,"text":"for food. At the moment, we are trashing our land"},{"time":827053,"text":"to grow food that no one eats."},{"time":829567,"text":"Stop wasting food. Thank you very much. (Applause)"},{"time":832663,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}